OL,7,FShe has some treasured photos of the
OL,8,Ftwo of them together: a devoted mum
OL,9,Fcradling her as a baby, and later a
OL,10,Flively toddler - clutching an ice
OL,11,Fcream and a fistful of Wotsits -
OL,12,Fcuddled up on a sun lounger.
OL,14,FThose pictures are so precious because
OL,15,Fthey provide one of the few links
OL,16,FLydia has with the mum who was gone
OL,17,Fall too soon. And whose face she
OL,18,Fsimply cannot recall.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G2/13
